 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Feb. 6: IVRCL Infrastructures amp; Projects Ltd today said it would split equity shares in the 1:5 ratio. The board has approved the splitting of shares of Rs 10 each into five of Rs 2 each, subject to shareholders? approval at the extraordinary general meeting scheduled for March 3, the company told Bombay Stock Exchange. After the split, IVRCL?s authorised share capital of Rs 40 crore will consist of 17.50 crore shares of Rs 2 each and 2.50 crore preference shares of Rs 2 each.

 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Royal Orchid today listed at a premium of Rs 240.10 on the BSE. The scrip had touched an intra-day high of Rs 265 before closing at Rs 231.30. The firm manages four hotels in the country.

 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Ranbaxy Laboratories has entered into a joint venture deal with South African Community Investment Holdings to market and sell its range of anti-retroviral products in the African markets.

 Mumbai, Feb. 6: Sebi has clamped down on five brokers for violating its regulations regarding fraudulent and unfair trade practices.

